=== ROAR CARD DECK — iPark / AUB Office of Innovation & Transformation ===

CORE VALUES: TIE
- Teamwork
- Integrity
- Excellence

=== CARD 1: SHOW UP WHERE IT MATTERS ===
Strong teams require shared presence.
- Minimum three days per week in the office
- Be present for critical meetings and university events
- Do not use hybrid work to avoid accountability
- Support colleagues during high-impact moments

=== CARD 2: IF DECIDED, WRITE IT DOWN ===
Clarity prevents confusion.
- Every decision requires a written summary
- Capture actions, owners, and deadlines
- Clarify who sends the summary
- Ask recipients to confirm or correct

=== CARD 3: THE 24 HOURS RULE ===
Silence erodes trust.
- Acknowledge emails and calls within 24-48 hours
- Address what you can immediately
- Set expectations for full responses
- Proactively update if delays occur

=== CARD 4: RESPECT THE CLOCK ===
Punctuality reflects the discipline.
- Arrive on time to meetings and calls
- Join fully prepared and ready to start
- Inform the organizer if you will be late
- Notify no later than 10 minutes before start time

=== CARD 5: NO LAST MINUTE SURPRISES ===
Consistency strengthens trust.
- Do not cancel meetings at the last minute
- Notify participants early on
- Provide notice at least one hour in advance
- Reserve no-shows for true emergencies only

=== CARD 6: SAY WHAT YOU DO — DO WHAT YOU SAY ===
Proactive communication preserves trust.
- End meetings with clear commitments
- Honor agreed deadlines
- If at risk, notify early
- Propose a realistic revised timeline

=== CARD 7: ESCALATE EARLY ===
Escalation is professional, not personal.
- Follow up once when inputs are delayed
- Set a new deadline
- If still unresolved, copy your manager
- Surface risks before they become failures

=== CARD 8: CAMERAS ON ===
Visibility strengthens connection.
- Keep cameras on during virtual meetings
- Promote engagement and accountability
- Support effective communication
- Turn off only for technical limitations

=== CARD 9: IF IT IS NOT IN THE SYSTEM, IT DOES NOT EXIST ===
Transparency protects everyone.
- All requests require a system ticket (e.g. TDx)
- Do not track work via email or chat alone
- Guide stakeholders to submit properly
- Create tickets on their behalf when needed

=== CARD 10: SEE SOMETHING — DO SOMETHING ===
Accountable sustains excellence.
- Address conflicting behaviors responsibly
- Do not ignore repeated lapses
- Raise concerns early on
- Treat accountability as shared responsibility

=== CARD 11: OWN THE DECISION ===
Alignment accelerates execution.
- Accept final decisions, even if not preferred
- Avoid passive resistance or reopening debate
- Act as an ambassador for the chosen direction
- Support implementation with positivity

=== CARD 12: BE A GOOD STEWARD ===
Stewardship protects credibility.
- Spend only where value is clear
- Avoid unnecessary complexity or scope creep
- Optimize contracts, licenses, and vendors
- Be disciplined with travel and discretionary costs

=== CLOSING ===
We ROAR Together.
American University of Beirut — Office of Innovation & Transformation
